Not everyone spent today with flowers and smiles.
Some of us mothered in silence.
Some of us mothered too soon.
Some of us became the women we needed when we were children.

Today, i honored HER.
The quiet caretaker inside me.
The girl who raised grown-ups.
The woman who is finally learning to raise herself.

To every soul reparenting in the shadows—i see you.
Especially my fellow indian daughters, the silent cycle breakers.
This is for US.
.
.
.

Dear Phoenix,

Everything changes—time, people, circumstances, everything. The only constant is YOU.

Evolution demands sacrifice. Growth requires shedding. You cannot hold on to what no longer serves you and expect to thrive.

I am living proof that letting go is not loss; it is Liberation. If you keep pulling at what is meant to fall away, you will only leave yourself bruised. Trust the unraveling. Let fate work its magic, but remember, MAGIC WITHOUT EFFORT IS A WASTED SPELL.

Give your all. Pour in your 100%, but never forget yourself in the process. Because at the end of it all, it’s not about them. It’s about YOU.

Make sure YOU are proud.
Make sure YOU are fulfilled.
Make sure YOU feel good at the end of the day.

And when the dust settles, when the echoes fade, when the night feels too heavy, remember, the fire in you is older than the storms around you. You were made to rise.

Yours truly,
Nishtha xxx

This is what I’d tell you if you’ve been feeling invisible lately:

Firstly— it’s okay.
This feeling is universal.
We’re human. We’re bound to feel.

And recognizing that you feel this way, just acknowledging it, is the first and the hardest step.
So if you’ve done that… I’m proud of you already.🫂

Now ask yourself this:
📣‘Who have you been invisible to?’

Because here’s the thing —
If you’re taking the effort, showing up, speaking up…
Then your work will bear the fruit.
Maybe not today, maybe not this week but it will, in due time.
Some things aren’t in our control but your EFFORT is and that matters more than you know.

And second—
📣‘Why do you even want to be visible to them in the first place?’

Who are you doing this for?
This life is YOURS.
This journey is yours.
And that’s part of the Awakening; realizing that you don’t need to prove your worth to anyone.

So please don’t let someone’s silence make you forget your voice.

Your only job is to take care of YOU.
To show up for YOU.
To remember that YOU deserve your own love and attention before anyone else’s.

✨Because nothing in this world gets to decide if you’re worthy or not.
You are.
Even when it’s quiet.
Even when it’s slow.
Even when no one is clapping yet.

Sometimes…
🤍the loudest breakthroughs happen in the seasons when no one is watching.

You’re not invisible. 
You’re just evolving and that’s powerful.
You are powerful, sweetheart!

— N (still growing just like you)
.
.

Stop blaming life. Understand this instead.

You’re not behind. You’re not too late.
You’re just in the middle of figuring it out.
And maybe… that’s what growth really looks like.

So sip that coffee. Breathe. Write it all down.
But most of all—keep showing up.
Not for perfection. Not for applause.
But because you haven’t come this far for nothing.

Don’t forget who you’re doing this for.
And that, my love, is reason enough. 🖤
.

Sometimes it’s not about fixing everything.
It’s not about having the answers, the plan, or the energy.
It’s just about… showing up.
With pain. With fatigue. With a heart that’s been through too much.

Because strength doesn’t always roar.
Sometimes it just whispers:
“I’m still here.”

And that alone is powerful.

🎥 Save this for the days you forget your own strength.
🖤 Share it with someone else who needs to remember theirs.

That’s the proof that love exists. Right there—in the reflection.

Hope gets hard. Life feels heavy. But here’s the thing: this is your life.

Let nobody tell you what to think, what to change or what you deserve.
Yes, you can listen, learn, even receive guidance but the final say? That’s yours.
Because this is your life. Your journey.
And the truth is, no one can walk it for you.

So take that stand.
Protect your peace.
Hold your head high with self-respect.
And start, even if you don’t know how because figuring it out IS the journey.

Self-love. Self-worth. Self-trust.
The moment you give yourself these things, the world starts reflecting it back.

✨ You deserve the life you dream of but only you can build it.
Now go claim it.🖤✨
